text:
On my quest for herbal Bak Kut Teh, found this stall at Jurong West Hawker Centre, serving a dark broth along with off-the-bone pork ribs, beancurd skin etc in a claypot! To balance the meal, we had a plate of Iceberg lettuce drizzled with oyster/sesame sauce (tasted like a mix of both).

IG @pingguo301
The dry bak kut teh is good, not common to find Malaysian style in Singapore hawker scene

Very nice bak kut teh. We ate the herbal bak kut teh and dry bak kut teh. Both are nice. The dry bak kut teh was very flavourful and there was alot of cuttlefish  shreds inside. Highly recommended ðŸ¥°
